content.description: This route is actually pretty great. You get to pull a sweet roof on jugs! It's a little dirty but this route just needs traffic to get really good.
content.protection: Gear to 3 inches, doubles in the hand sizes and some small stuff.  2 bolt and slings anchor.
content.location: Just to the right of the bolted 5.9+ (shared anchor)

content.description: This is the right most route on the wall. Look for the interesting flared crack system with a horizontal crack that leads to a perfect hand crack about 2/3 of the way up the route. Climb this sublime hand crack and exit onto the face to the left. Somehow climb the moves on the face and ponder at the 5.9 rating in the guide, or bail out to the right and skip the last bolt.
content.protection: gear to two inches, two button heads and a 2 bolt ASCA anchor.
content.location: This route in on the right hand side of the wall just before the wet gully.

content.description: This quality sport route climbs the arete and face  just right of the low roof with detached flakes. Pinches and side pulls on steep ground lead to enjoyable crimps.
content.location: Just right of the low roof with detached flakes.

content.description: This route climbs a left leaning flake into a splitter hand crack near the top of the route. Similar in feel to checkered dog at Monolith just a little easier.
content.location: This route is just right of the unknown 5.9 and left of the bolted 5.11 face climb

content.description: This is the route you came for. Climb featured rock past 2 bolts to intriguing corner moves. Follow the corner as it arches right around the huge upper triangular roof. Finish above the roof or top out  the wall for another anchor high on a boulder.
content.location: Shallow corner at the left side of the wall.

content.description: This wall sees little traffic but is worthy destination for a day of cragging with a good selection of route types and grades. The area recieves sun for most of the day and dries quickly after the rain.
